---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import GalleryLightbox from '../../components/GalleryLightbox.astro';

const title = "Atelier B — Brand Identity for a Contemporary Architecture Studio | Aenea";
const description = "Atelier B is a brand identity by Aenea for a contemporary architecture and design studio — a refined visual identity, logotype, and colour system built on space, proportion, and restraint.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <Navbar current="work" />

  <main>
    <section class="proj-intro wrap">
      <a href="/work" class="back-link"><span aria-hidden="true">←</span> Selected Work</a>
      <span class="eyebrow proj-cat">Brand Identity</span>
      <h1 class="proj-title">Atelier B</h1>
      <p class="proj-lead">A complete brand identity for a contemporary architecture and design studio — a refined visual system built on space, proportion, and restraint, designed to feel permanent and quietly confident.</p>
      <div class="proj-meta">
        <div><div class="meta-k">Service</div><div class="meta-v">Brand Identity</div></div>
        <div><div class="meta-k">Sector</div><div class="meta-v">Architecture &amp; Design</div></div>
        <div><div class="meta-k">Year</div><div class="meta-v">2025</div></div>
        <div><div class="meta-k">Deliverables</div><div class="meta-v">Logotype, Identity system, Guidelines</div></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <figure class="bleed" data-lightbox>
      <img src="/atelier-b-hero.jpg" alt="Atelier B brand identity — full visual identity system for a contemporary architecture studio, by Aenea" />
    </figure>

    <section class="case wrap">
      <div class="case-label"><span class="idx">01</span><span class="eyebrow">Overview</span></div>
      <div class="case-body">
        <p>Atelier B is conceived as a contemporary design studio where space, proportion, and restraint take centre stage — a place where ideas are refined, stripped back, and shaped with intent. The brief was a brand identity that could carry that same discipline across every touchpoint.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="wrap">
      <div class="pair">
        <figure class="ph s7 r43" data-lightbox><img src="/atelier-b-1.jpg" alt="Atelier B logotype and wordmark — architecture studio visual identity by Aenea" /></figure>
        <figure class="ph s5 r45" data-lightbox><img src="/atelier-b-2.jpg" alt="Atelier B typography and brand system detail" /></figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case wrap">
      <div class="case-label"><span class="idx">02</span><span class="eyebrow">The Identity</span></div>
      <div class="case-body">
        <p>No ornament for ornament&rsquo;s sake — every element exists for a reason. The logotype and typography carry quiet authority: clean, confident, and deliberate, communicating permanence without leaning on nostalgia. Subtle refinements in spacing and form give the identity its edge — fresh, contemporary, and unmistakably high-end.</p>
        <p>The colour palette is built to live effortlessly across digital and physical environments. Muted neutrals and refined tones let the brand adapt without losing character — on a website, in project documentation, or as studio signage.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="wrap">
      <div class="pair">
        <figure class="ph s5 r45" data-lightbox><img src="/atelier-b-3.jpg" alt="Atelier B colour palette and brand application across touchpoints" /></figure>
        <figure class="ph s7 r43" data-lightbox><img src="/atelier-b-4.jpg" alt="Atelier B identity across studio collateral and signage" /></figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case wrap">
      <div class="case-label"><span class="idx">03</span><span class="eyebrow">Outcome</span></div>
      <div class="case-body">
        <p>Atelier B earns attention through balance, discipline, and detail. The identity works as a framework — letting the studio&rsquo;s architecture and design work breathe, while holding a strong, cohesive presence across the brand.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="next wrap">
      <a href="/work/golden-hour" class="next-link">
        <span class="next-k">Next project</span>
        <span class="next-title">Golden Hour <span class="arr" aria-hidden="true">↗</span></span>
        <span class="next-cat">Logo Design</span>
      </a>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
  <GalleryLightbox />
</Layout>